Comics at the BBC must go through a lengthy process to get some jokes on air because the Corporation is extra-ary about causing offence , an editor at the company .
Chris Sussman , executive editor for comedy revealed particular jokes have to go through ` quite a lot of layers ' to be approved .
Some jokes even have to be looked over by director general Lord Hall .
Comedian Frankie Boyle has criticised the BBC about its cautious attitude towards comedy .